commitResults.messageTitle: Reflect change in todo list in text file
commitResults.messageBody:
Text file does not reflect change in internal list of todo tasks.

If the change is not reflected, progress is not correctly saved
across instances.

Add some file modifying methods to facilitate functionalities such
as:
1. Add Task
2. Delete Task (given index n)

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'branch-level-7'
Implement Date functionality into Deadline and Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Dates are just strings.

So, users could input deadlines that made no sense (i.e I have a
homework deadline by apple).

Restrict date format to yyyy-mm-dd to not only facilitate logical
dates in the list, but to open up to future date comparison features
as well.

commitResults.messageTitle: Separate methods into different classes based on functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Everything is in one class (except tasks which was done before)

Divide methods into classes based on their usage (i.e Storage
methods goes to Storage class, etc)

Code is more modular and clean this way
